stories.text:
HN Community,

I found booking.com have shown different price for me and my friend, as a higher level booking.com user, the price I have is $10 higher (10% mark up) than my friend. I am still using the app to book hotels. I think this probably happens in all apps. What's a viable solution for end users? Always book with unregistered users and have a compare website for hotels? I know this is not a technical question, but it opens up a space for a new app. TripAdvisor probably is fine since it displays different prices from a few providers.

What do you all think? Targeted pricing is reality now.
stories.title: Ask HN: Booking.com shows different price for different users

stories.text:
I asked this question in a thread recently but I was too late in posting to receive a reply. The article being discussed mentioned offhandedly that rust has no formally defined memory model.

What does it mean for a language to have a formally defined memory model? What benefits does having one confer? Is it hard to specify one? Why?
stories.title: Ask HN: What does a formal memory model entail?
